Package edu.ncsu.csc216.pack_scheduler.course

Class Activity

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.ncsu.csc216.pack_scheduler.course.Activity
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Conflict
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Course
    public abstract class Activity
extends java.lang.Object
implements Conflict
    Activity Class is the abstract class that encompasses the Course and Event Classes An activity must have a title, start time, end time, meeting days, and the fields the concrete class requires (course or event). Activities have two versions of display arrays, a short and long one to display in the schedule tabs.
    Author:
    Ashten Herr

      • setMeetingDaysAndTime

        public void setMeetingDaysAndTime​(java.lang.String meetingDays,
                                  int startTime,
                                  int endTime)
        setMeetingDaysAndTime checks the startTime and endTime parameters, which can not be greater than 2399 or less than 0000. setMeetingDaysAndTime also checks that end time is greater than start time otherwise IAE is thrown. meetingDays Parameter is checked in child classes.
        Parameters:
        meetingDays - - meeting days as a string
        startTime - - start time as military time
        endTime - - end time as military time
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if startTime is greater than endTime
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if an invalid military time is given. Hours can not be less than 0 or above 23 and minutes can not be less than 0 or above 59.

      • getMeetingString

        public java.lang.String getMeetingString()
        Returns a string with the meeting days and the start and end times formatted in regular time. Format is meetingDays formatted start time - formatted end time ex - MW 1:35PM-2:35PM. If the class is Arranged then "Arranged" is returned as the meeting string.
        Returns:
        the meeting string as a string with meeting days start time and end time

      • checkConflict

        public void checkConflict​(Activity possibleConflictingActivity)
                   throws ConflictException
        checkConflict checks the current instance of activity to another activity to see if the activities have a conflicting time slots. if the two activities do have a conflicting time slot which includes an overlapping day and time value that is inclusive a ConflictException is thrown. The only exception to this rule are Arranged courses which are allowed to have an overlapping time slot with other arranged courses.
        Specified by:
        checkConflict in interface Conflict
        Parameters:
        possibleConflictingActivity - - Activity that could have a possible time conflict with the current instance.
        Throws:
        ConflictException - - if the current instance of Activity and the possibleConflictingActivity have an overlapping time on the same day. (Excludes Arranged Times)
